Bumpkin Tales Part 4  
<br />
 
<br />
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
<br />
 12.01.00:0920  
<br />
 
<br />
 
<br />
 Dumbly ran ahead of Dudley to scan the terrain. They had been traveling for days now, and were inching for a fight. Dumbly found a small opening in the side of a hill of sand. They were in an area known as the common lands, an alien and unfamiliar place to both of them. 
<br />

<br />
Dumbly entered the small door as Dudley huffed to catch up. Dumbly entered the abandoned mansion. He found only a few hardened adventurers in the small entryway into what he found was called Befallen. He ran around a corner and found himself face to face with the lost soul named Lrrod. Most of Lrrod's flesh had been long eaten or rotted away, but a strange light shone in his dead eyes as he cackled mindlessly at Dumbly. Dumbly drew his sword and his claws, which were given to him by a kind druid named Angus. 
<br />

<br />
Dumbly readied himself for a hard battle as the bony fingers of Lrrod's skeletal hand raked Dumbly's chest. Dumbly slashed and parried, cutting minor pieces of bone from the bony frame, but he found that most of his attacks had no effect on the undead man. Dumbly kicked Lrrod in the ribcage, shattering its fragile ribs like dry sticks, still Lrrod cackled mindlessly on, scratching at Dumbly's face and chest with its bony fingers. Dumbly managed to cut one of the hands off, but Lrrod fought with the sharp point where its hand had once been. Dumbly ducked and parried every thrust, but he was getting tired, and the skeleton knew no fatigue. Dumbly finally saw his opening, and beheaded the cackling apparition. Lrrod's boned fell to the ground, leaving only a few coins and a pile of bone fragments. 
<br />

<br />
Dumbly kept the coins and journeyed further into the hallway. He heard the talking of a living being. Thinking this was a friend, Dumbly walked blindly into the room. The shadow knight turned his head and stared at the young warrior. Dumbly swung his sword and caught the shadow knight in the chest. With his dying breath, the shadow knight cast a spell and knocked Dumbly down a well behind him. 
<br />

<br />
The last thing Dumbly saw was the bones on the floor below him before the blackness came.  
