Bumpkin Tales Part 5  
<br />
 
<br />
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
<br />
 12.01.00:0920  
<br />
 
<br />
 
<br />
 Dumbly awoke in a small pool of his own blood. His head hurt and he could vaguely remember how he got down here. He sat up slowly, noting the pain in his left arm. He figured that due to the pain it was broken, and he knew when he tried to pick up his sword that the arm would be useless in a fight. He painfully made a splint out of the bones littering the ground, and put his sword in his belt. His infravision did little to help penetrate the suffocating darkness that enveloped him. He walked foreword a few steps, and was beset upon by a large host of angry, and strong undead. Dumbly was strong, but these ghouls and skeletons were stronger than anything that he had ever seen. Even with both arms, Dumbly knew he wouldn't have been able to take them all. For one of the first times in his life, the mighty warrior fled. Dumbly ran blindly through the sunken mansion called Befallen. He looked for an escape route, or somewhere that he could hide away from these ungodly creatures. He finally came to a large door, and attempted to open it. He found that it was locked. Placing his back to the door, he readied his claws for battle. Suddenly, the door behind him flew open, and Dumbly landed in the lap of a cleric. Warning him of the impending danger from the train of undead, Dumbly continued his flight through the underground mansion. Shouting a warning to anyone who he came across, Dumbly ran as fast as his little legs could carry him. He reached the foyer and stopped. He didn't know why, but he wanted to see what he had caused. A huge train of skeletons, ghouls, and necromancers followed him. Dumbly then ran as fast as he could out the door, knowing that the dark magic that animated these ungodly abominations could not keep them alive if they crossed the threshold of the house out into the sand. Dumbly ran until he found an inn, in the middle of a small forest somewhere in the commonlands. He paid for a room and then set down his armor and bags. As soon as he sat on the bed, he fell deeply into a peaceful slumber. 
<br />

<br />
Hotil sat outside Dumbly's window, listening to his deep breathing. He let his rage grow at the Bumpkins. Hotil had been in Befallen looking for a new dagger, which was held by one of the dark magi whom had animated the undead. He had been on one of the lowest levels of the mansion, and had killed his partner to escape, taking a potion of teleportation from the dead druids hand. He had been seen by the same cleric whom Dumbly had run into. The cleric was running from the train. Hottil had tried to kill the man, but his god had lifted him up and put him in a place where he was safe. Hottil had no such powers, his god was the god of hate, and Hottil did not look foreword to meeting him. Hottil had been able to dodge the train and avoid them on their way back to their homes, but his hatred for Dudley grew. Dudley would come soon. All Hottil had to do was follow Dumbly and he would find him, then, revenge would be his. He would wait.  
<br />

