Bumpkin Tales Part 6  
<br />
 
<br />
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
<br />
 12.01.00:0920  
<br />
 
<br />
 
<br />
 Hottil wiped the blood off of his blade. The lifeless body of the innkeeper slumped down into a pool of blood. Hottil walked around the small inn, looking for anything that his prey might have left behind. Finding only empty bottles of honey mead, he moved on to follow the halfling's trail. 
<br />

<br />
Two nights ago, Hottil had been sitting out side of Dumbly's window. He had been waiting for the young warrior to leave and meet up with his brother, Dudley. Hottil had made the mistake of falling asleep, and Dumbly had awoken and left before Hottil woke up. In his rage, Hottil attracted the attention of the innkeeper who had attempted to stop Hottil from destroying the inn in his fit of rage. Hottil had told the innkeeper a story of Dumbly murdering his company of friends, and of Hottil seeking revenge. The innkeeper, believing Hottil's story, had invited him in for food and drink. Hottil had killed him as he ate. Hottil felt no remorse for the slain innkeeper, just one more conquered obstacle in his quest to extract revenge on the warrior who had ruined Hottil's life. 
<br />

<br />
The Kodiak was huge, and enraged. It had watched as Dudley and Dumbly had slaughtered her young just to have them make their funny sounds. She rose on her huge hind legs and bellowed a challenge at the two young warriors. Taking up a roar of their own, the two small halflings launched themselves at the enraged giant. The Kodiak had never felt such pain, as the weapons of the two warriors flew in as quickly as a swarm of stinging bees. They flowed with an inner rhythm beautiful to behold in their dance of death. Both worked with each other, one's sword finding the gap that the other just opened up. The Kodiak did not stand a chance. One final roar, more like a moan, escaped the giant bears bloody frame, its last breath sinking to a small gasp as its life's blood formed a puddle around the huge mass of flesh. Dumbly wiped his claws on a clean spot of fur. 
<br />

<br />
"Wow." A beautiful tenor voice exclaimed, "You two are awesome!" Taking a large swig of honey mead Dumbly replied, "Dumbly and Dudley mighty warriors." "I know that." Said the voice, "Would you two be interested in joining the Drunks of Tunare? By the way, my name is Kenluil." 
<br />

<br />
Hottil watched closely. The drunks of Tunare, what a laugh. They should be easy to best. He just needed a time to strike.  
