Bumpkin Tales Part 7  
<br />
 
<br />
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
<br />
 12.01.00:0920  
<br />
 
<br />
 
<br />
 The sun was hot in the desert. Dumbly was almost regretting his and Dudley's choice to sit and kill the bandits who frequented the area. South Ro was known for the bandits; they were not to be messed with. Dumbly and Dudley found this rumor to be a bit ovregzaderated. They dropped the bandits quick and hard when ever the bandits returned to their camp. They only had problems with the casters. They casters could do major damage to the Bumpkins using their powerful spells. Dudley had made the suggestion of killing them first, and that had seemed to be working out for the time being. They had made large amounts of cash from the valuable weapons that the bandits had, and they were becoming better warriors. The fighting experience that they were gaining was immense. They could barely believe how much they had grown in the past few days in the desert. "Dumbly, they up again." Yawned Dudley. "Dumbly see." Mumbled Dumbly,"Why can't they let Dumbly sleep more? Dumbly still sore from the earlier battle. Why fight so much? Dumbly not like fight that much, make Dumbly hurt lots." "Dumbly weak." Dudley chuckled, "Dumbly need fight to make Dumbly strong like Dudley" "Okies." Said Dumbly, putting his armor on. "Dumbly will race Dudley to bandits!" 
<br />

<br />
The bandits were returning from a plundering raid. They had gotten some of their best loot ever, and all five of them were carrying bronze weapons. They returned to find their camp empty, not unusual, due to the fact that the rest were probably out plundering. They had just set their heavy bags when Dumbly and Dudley struck. 
<br />

<br />
The first bandit fell to Dudley's two-handed sword. Dudley caught a second in the leg with an upward swing. Dumbly flew into two of the bandits, slitting one's thought as he flew by. The second brought his sword up in a parry. Dumbly ran his langseax along the blade to his point's hand, and then brought his claws down onto the bandit's unprotected shoulder. The bandit howled in pain and shifted his stance, unable to wield his sword with his bad arm. Dumbly used this to his advantage as he overpowered the bandit with his langseax and sliced at openings with his claws. The bandit tried one last time to impale Dumbly, but Dumbly easily parried the desperate lunge. Dumbly brought both of his weapons in a brutal x across the bandit's chest, neatly disemboweling him. The bandit groaned, not believing that the mess on the sand was once his innards. He died with a confused look on his face. The fifth hobbled off, shouting for help. Just as he thought he might make it, the two barbed shafts sticking out of his back forever silenced his cries. He pitched into the sand with a small groan and fell into eternity. 
<br />

<br />
Dudley and Dumbly were cleaning off their blades and going over the bodies looking for loot when a drunken dwarven cleric and an odd Elven mage approached them. " Hail and well met Bumpkins, my name is Madrix and I am a member of your guild, the drunks. My dwarven companion is Glendore, but he is inebriated to the point that we would not be able to understand anything he tried to say. Would you two like to join us and a few other drunks in a romp through the oasis of mar? We are trying to rid the beach of the vile crocodiles." 
<br />

<br />
Sitting on a pillar out in the ocean, Dumbly poked Glendore. "Uh Mad?" Dumbly said "Dumbly thinks that Glen is sick or something." "Nonsense. He is just passed out, he does that a lot." "Oh, ok. Dumbly will watch over his so he don't die." 
<br />

<br />
So Dumbly and Madrix sat, waiting for Glendore to wake up so they could join the rest of the drunks. As they sat, a bard ran up. "Look Out!" The bard gasped, "There is a specter coming this w…" His last word was never finished. A scythe cleaved the bard neatly in two, and Dumbly stared straight into the face of death. Floating a foot or two above the ground, the specter was every inch death, even carrying the scythe. Dumbly tried to fight it, but it moved towards its true target. Glendore never awoke, it struck him down where he slept, and then it floated off, killing anyone stupid enough to be in its way. 
<br />

<br />
Hottil watched and laughed. He had aggravated the apportion, and had guided it towards the pillar where Dumbly was sitting. He was a ways away, but he was sure that the small shape that had died was that of his enemy, Dumbly. If killing Dumbly was that easy, than Dudley would soon follow. 
<br />

<br />
Dumbly ran to the small corpse that was once his drunken friend and wept. Leaning his head on Glendore's, Dumbly wept like a small child. Suddenly he heard something beautiful. Glendore was still alive, barely, but alive, and praying to his god. A small beam of light shone down from the heavens and enveloped the small form of Glendore. Blue spots of light swirled around his form until all his wounds were healed. Once he was done, he sat down, took out a bottle, and began to drink.  
