Bumpkin Tales Part 8  
<br />
 
<br />
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
<br />
 12.01.00:0920  
<br />
 
<br />
 
<br />
 Since Dudley had gone, Didley and Dodley had been without guidance. They were not ready to take on the challenge of keeping up the old Homestead, so they went to look for Maggendy. Dodley decided that he would try and find her in the east, so he headed out to Freeport, intending to go to Faydwar. His journey took him along many of the same roads as Dudley and Dumbly. He found many signs that his brothers had been this way, but he was never able to see any sign of Maggendy. 
<br />

<br />
Deciding to find Dudley and Dumbly to help him search, Dodley went south at Freeport into the desert, following their trail. He traveled without rest, all his energy devoted to finding his brothers. He was nearly mad with thirst when he stumbled into the oasis. He found a multitude of people fighting crocodiles, and decided that he would make camp along the beach. 
<br />

<br />
Hottil had lost Dumbly and Dudley. After he trained the specter on them, a sand giant had started attacking him. Hottil had to run and train the giant on another person to avoid dying. That person had died with a sad confused look on his face as the sand giant's huge fists pounded him into a bloody pulp. Hottil was walking around trying to find some trace of his prey when he camp upon a small camp. The camp seemed hauntingly familiar to him. Thinking that there might be money or water inside, Hottil went into the camp. 
<br />

<br />
Dodley heard the small crash as someone tripped over his staff. He opened one eye and scanned the room. Seeing nothing out of the ordinary, he closed his eye. He laid his hand on top of the handle of his scimitar, which was on the ground beside him. He felt hot breath on his face and slashed at the intruder. The intruder let out a gasp of pain and stumbled backwards, cursing. Dodley attempted to get in a sitting position, but the intruder kicked him back to the ground. Dodley attempted to slash at the intruder, but his block was parried and he felt cold steel as a dagger slid between his ribs. He clasped the dagger in both hands and sunk back to the floor. 
<br />

<br />
Hottil pulled his dagger out of Dodley's chest and cleaned it off. He spat contemptusally on the small form, struggling for breath. Hottil decided to let him die a slow and painful death. Dodley's breathing became more labored as more blood flowed into his damaged lung. He gave one final shudder and lay still. 
<br />

<br />
Hottil smiled at the small corpse lying on the ground. He knew it that murdering Dodley would send Dudley to find him. Hottil would be ready this time. He would finish Dudley as easily as he had slain his brother. Behind his bravado however, Hottil feared that his actions would drive Dudley into a rage, which would make him much harder to defeat. Still, Hottil thought he could still win. 
<br />

<br />
Didley finally made it to Qyenos. He had been traveling for many months, and was glad to finally reach his destination. He hoped that he could not only find Maggendy, but also get taught the clerical arts by the cleric guild in Qyenos, one of the best in the world. He hoped that with his gift from his god that he could find his sister. 
<br />

<br />
Dudley noticed a small, ransacked camp as he and Dudley were walking to Freeport. They decided to investigate. In the middle of the small camp, they found a small bundle. Dudley opened it up. A cry split the midday calm of the oasis. "Aieeeeee!"  
<br />

